TITLE: Dolphins' Tyreek Hill left in the dust by young football player at Miami camp
SUMMARY: Dolphins wide receiver Tyreek Hill was giving back to the youth with his football camp in Miami on Saturday, but he didn't expect one camper to embarrass him on the field.

TITLE: Imam stabbed during prayers at New Jersey Omar Mosque: reports
SUMMARY: A prayer leader, known as an imam, was stabbed twice Sunday at a mosque in Paterson, New Jersey. The suspect's name has not been released, nor a motive.

TITLE: Social media secret profiles: Does Facebook have your info?
SUMMARY: If you use social media, it's worth clearing out all the things you've looked up. Here are easy steps to save yourself some potential embarrassment later.

TITLE: Senate chaplain doubles down after saying 'thoughts and prayers' are not enough after Nashville shooting
SUMMARY: Senate Chaplain the Rev. Barry Black said there is "a time when action is required" after calls from Democrats to reintroduce gun control legislation after Nashville school shooting.

TITLE: Florida police arrest third juvenile suspect in triple homicide
SUMMARY: The Marion County, Florida sheriff's office, with the help of U.S. Marshals and the Lake County Sheriff's Office arrested a third suspect in connection to a triple homicide.

TITLE: Gov. Gavin Newsom offers DeSantis political advice, says he will get 'rolled by Trump': 'Pack up and wait'
SUMMARY: Gov. Gavin Newsom offered Gov. Ron DeSantis some political advice during an interview on Sunday and said he would get "rolled" by Donald Trump in an election.

TITLE: Soros-backed policy group notches victory with Biden's transgender Title IX rules
SUMMARY: A group bankrolled with nearly $10 million from a George Soros nonprofit notched a victory from the Biden administration's proposed Title IX rule, which brings in gender identity.

TITLE: Former AG issues chilling warning that left's agenda is 'leading to horrific crimes'
SUMMARY: Former acting U.S. Attorney General Matthew Whitaker shared his concerns for the left's push for gun control amid rising crime.

TITLE: LSU star Angel Reese receives support from Tony Yayo, creator of 'You Can't See Me' taunt
SUMMARY: LSU star Angel Reese received support from the originator of the "You Can't See Me" taunt in the wake of the backlash she received from doing the celebratory gestures.

TITLE: Dem senator accuses Trump of leaving Biden with ‘bad options’ for disastrous Afghanistan withdrawal
SUMMARY: Sen. Ben Cardin appeared on "FOX News Sunday" and said that President Biden was not left with any good options concerning the Afghanistan withdrawal in 2021 because of Trump.

TITLE: UFC star praises Trump, DeSantis, leads crowd in ‘Let’s go, Brandon' chant
SUMMARY: UFC Star Jorge Masvidal praised former President Trump and Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis after the final fight of his career, going on to lead a 'Let's go, Brandon' chant.

TITLE: 'Fox News Sunday' on April 9, 2023
SUMMARY: This week on 'Fox News Sunday,' host Shannon Bream welcomed Sen. Ben Cardin, Sen. Lindsey Graham, and more to discuss the week's top political headlines.

TITLE: Julian Assange's family grills government's 'over-classification' of documents: 'A problem for democracy'
SUMMARY: Julian Assange's father and brother defended his actions of leaking military information during a recent appearance on Fox Nation's 'Piers Morgan: Uncensored.'

TITLE: Trump attorney pushes back after NBC host asks if Trump is holding classified docs for payout: 'Cheap shot'
SUMMARY: James Trusty, an attorney representing Donald Trump, called accusations that Trump was looking for a financial settlement over classified documents a "cheap shot."

TITLE: Leaked Pentagon documents claim Israel’s Mossad encouraged protests against Netanyahu
SUMMARY: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and the Mossad denied reports Sunday that Israel's intelligence agency had encouraged protests against Netanyahu's judicial reform efforts.

TITLE: CNN presses Rep. Ocasio-Cortez over claims Biden admin should 'ignore' abortion ruling: 'Stunning position'
SUMMARY: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez was pressed by CNN's Dana Bash on Sunday about her call for the Biden administration to ignore the ruling on the abortion pill.

TITLE: Barr slams Trump as weak candidate, makes bold prediction for 2024 election
SUMMARY: Former Attorney General Bill Barr said he views former President Trump as the "weakest of the Republican candidates," expecting him to lose to President Biden in the 2024 general election.

TITLE: Religious liberty nonprofit blasts bill banning protests near drag shows: 'Deranged parody of public law'
SUMMARY: Liberty Coalition Canada founder Michael Thiessen blasted a recent provincial bill in Ontario that would criminalize protests and "offensive remarks" around drag shows.

TITLE: Two Florida women arrested after taunting, abusing elderly woman on live stream 'pieces of crap,' sheriff says
SUMMARY: Two healthcare workers in Florida have been arrested after allegedly taunting, abusing an elderly woman with dementia and live streaming it, Sheriff Wayne Ivey says.

TITLE: Lindsey Graham lambasts Biden White House's review of botched Afghanistan exodus: 'Political whitewash'
SUMMARY: Sen. Lindsey Graham, R-S.C. grilled the Biden administration's report on the Afghanistan withdrawal Sunday, criticizing claims that Trump created conditions for the catastrophe.

TITLE: AOC claims there is 'crime wave' within GOP after saying officials should ignore court rulings
SUMMARY: New York Democratic Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez argued there is a crime wave within the Republican Party, and cited Trump and Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas.

TITLE: Norfolk Southern train cars derail, spilling diesel and oil; 2 taken to hospital
SUMMARY: Two crew members were briefly hospitalized after a Norfolk Southern train derailed in Alabama on Easter Sunday. Officials say there is no hazardous materials threat.

TITLE: Five empty Norfolk Southern train cars derail in Pittsburgh
SUMMARY: It was not immediately clear what caused five empty Norfolk Southern train cars to derail in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, on Saturday. No injuries were reported.

TITLE: Jim Nantz appears to make LIV Golf crack as Brooks Koepka finishes up third round of Masters
SUMMARY: Jim Nantz appeared to make a LIV Golf joke at the expense of Brooks Koepka on Sunday as players finished up the third round of the Masters.

TITLE: Missouri boy delivers hundreds of Easter baskets to children in need: 'Helping kids smile'
SUMMARY: Since he was three years old, Luke Flerlage has been volunteering with Alleluia Baskets in O'Fallon, Missouri, providing Easter baskets for the under privileged community.
